<p>
<seg id=1> Several million people throughout Russia held an anti-President Yeltsin demonstration on Wednesday, demanding that the government pay wages that are in arrears. </seg>
<seg id=2> However, the actual number of people who actually took part in the demonstrations was much smaller than the 40 million people estimated by the organizers. </seg>
<seg id=3> A small crowd of demonstrators gathered outside the Kremlin in Moscow, with many people waving the Communist flag. </seg>
<seg id=4> Presidential hopeful Lebed spoke to crowds gathered in Krasnoyarsk, a city in Siberia. </seg>
<seg id=5> He indicated that Russian and Western investors had already tired of waiting for true economic reform. </seg>
</p>
